:::summary
Art history is the study of visual art and architecture across time, from the cave paintings of prehistoric humanity to the cathedrals of the Middle Ages and the masterpieces of the Renaissance. It is inseparable from the history of civilization itself — every great artistic tradition reflects the beliefs, values, and spiritual aspirations of the people who produced it. Understanding art history is essential for any classically educated person who wishes to understand Western culture and the Christian vision of beauty that has shaped it.
